               <p>WILLIAM RICHARD MORRIS. I was in <placeName id="t18300415-353-crimeloc1913">Fleet-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-353-crimeloc1913" type="placeName" value="Fleet-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-353-crimeloc1913" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-353-off1911 t18300415-353-crimeloc1913"></join> on the evening of the 7th of April - I felt a pull at my pocket, turned round, and a gentleman had the prisoner and the handkerchief in his hand, and charged him with taking it- he denied it; I had been walking arm-in-arm with a friend - this is my handkerchief.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-353-person2932">
                  GILES 
                  STEVENS
               <interp inst="t18300415-353-person2932" type="surname" value="STEVENS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-353-person2932" type="given" value="GILES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-353-person2932" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in Fleet-street, and saw the prisoner draw the handkerchief from that gentleman's pocket; I took hold of him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Were there not several persons about? A. There were two of his companions behind him, and he was close behind the prosecutor; I detained him, and took him to the watch-house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-353-person2933">
                  THOMAS 
                  WITHCOMB
               <interp inst="t18300415-353-person2933" type="surname" value="WITHCOMB"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-353-person2933" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-353-person2933" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer; I received the prisoner, and have the handkerchief.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had been to Whitechapel to see my sister - I came up with these gentlemen; I stepped off the edge of the payement to pass them, and the gentleman caught hold of me.</p>


